ng anything in the tests seems necessary! That should help capture the logs effectively.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering logger initialization**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking that LoggerFactory might initialize when the Log4j bridge loads, especially after settings are applied in a static block. I wonder if I can capture System.err for SimpleLogger since it defaults to output there and caches the print stream. I should really set \\\\\\\"org.slf4j.simpleLogger.logFile\\\\\\\" to \\\\\\\"System.out\\\\\\\" for clarity in captures. However, if initialized with System.err, it could hold references. Isolating this could get tricky, so maybe I need to look into using the slf4j-test library to help capture the output without adding too many dependencies!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_u2LTouBN47Qf2GzIHYCbeNn3|fc_0e6e3d51033a0b08016a003c9e18f48196889bfb69f5ed7722\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"build/tests/org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-to-slf4j:2.17.1/8154a1650b7d51d535220342bf9b6567.out\", \"limit\": 200}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 4658, \"output\": 1509, \"cacheRead\": 11264, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 17431, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778400391907, \"responseId\": \"resp_0e6e3d51033a0b08016a003c885c448196869252156e7b445c\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_u2LTouBN47Qf2GzIHYCbeNn3|fc_0e6e3d51033a0b08016a003c9e18f48196889bfb69f5ed7722\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Standard out\\n-----\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:extractPluginRequests UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:generatePluginAdapters UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:compileJava UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:compileGroovy UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:comp