(TCK)\\n\\nBuild Setup tasks\\n-----------------\\ninit - Initializes a new Gradle build.\\nupdateDaemonJvm - Generates or updates the Gradle Daemon JVM criteria.\\nwrapper - Generates Gradle wrapper files.\\n\\nHelp tasks\\n----------\\nartifactTransforms - Displays the Artifact Transforms that can be executed in root project 'reachability-metadata'.\\nbuildEnvironment - Displays all buildscript dependencies declared in root project 'reachability-metadata'.\\ndependencies - Displays all dependencies declared in root project 'reachability-metadata'.\\ndependencyInsight - Displays the insight into a specific dependency in root project 'reachability-metadata'.\\nhelp - Displays a help message.\\njavaToolchains - Displays the detected java toolchains.\\noutgoingVariants - Displays the outgoing variants of root project 'reachability-metadata'.\\nprojects - Displays the sub-projects of root project 'reachability-metadata'.\\nproperties - Displays the properties of root project 'reachability-metadata'.\\nresolvableConfigurations - Displays the configurations that can be resolved in root project 'reachability-metadata'.\\ntasks - Displays the tasks runnable from root project 'reachability-metadata'.\\n\\nMetadata tasks\\n--------------\\naddLibraryAsLatestMetadataIndexJson - Marks given coordinates as latest in metadata/group/artifact/index.json\\naddLibraryMetadataIndexJson - Adds given coordinates to metadata/group/artifact/index.json without changing the latest entry\\naddTestedVersion - Updates list of tested versions.\\nanalyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess - Resolves an external Maven coordinate and reports preserve/track dynamic-access totals\\ncheckAllowedDockerImages - Returns list of allowed docker images\\ncheckMetadataFiles - Checks content of metadata files for matching coordinates\\ncontribute - Generates metadata and prepares pull request for contibuting on metadata repository based on provided tests.\\ndiscoverArtifactMetadata - Uses a coding agent command to discover artifact metadata for a single coordinate and stores it under build/.\\nextractLibraryTestParams - Extracts TEST_PATH, LATEST_VERSION and TEST_COORDINATES for given coordinates (group:artifact[:version]). Writes them into GITHUB_ENV.\\nfetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions - Returns list of all libraries coordinates\\nfixTestNativeImageRun - Fix test that fails Native Image run for new library version.\\ngenerateAffectedSpringTestMatrix - Computes GA changes from git diff, scans Spring AOT for impacted tests, and emits a ready-to-use GitHub Actions matrix.\\ngenerateChangedCoordinatesMatrix - Returns matrix definition populated with coordinates of changed libraries\\ngenerateChangedCoordinatesOnlyMatrix - Returns a coordinate-only matrix definition populated with changed coordinates\\ngenerateChangedIndexFileCoordinatesList - Returns a list of changed coordinates for validation based on git diff\\ngenerateChangedMetadataTestMatrix - Returns matrix definition populated with changed coordinates and batched tested versions from metadata index files\\ngenerateDependencyGraph - Prints deps.dev dependency graph for matching coordinates\\ngenerateDynamicAccessCoverageReport - Generates a per-class dynamic-access coverage report for matching coordinates\\ngenerateDynamicAccessReport - Builds native tests and prints generated dynamic-access JSON report files for matching coordinates\\ngenerateInfrastructureChangedCoordinatesMatrix - Returns matrix definition populated with pre-selected coordinates when test infrastructure has changed\\ngenerateLibraryStats - Generates local library stats and updates stats/<group>/<artifact>/<metadata-version>/stats.json\\ngenerateMatrixBatchedCoordinates - Returns matrix definition populated with fractional batch coordinates (k/n)\\ngenerateMatrixMatchingCoordinates - Returns matrix definition populated with all matching coordinates\\ngenerateMetadata - Generates metadata based on provided tests.\\ngenerateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix - Returns matrix definition populated with newer library versions and CI environments\\ngenerateReadmeBadgeSummary - Generates current README metrics data, coverage Markdown, and updates README metrics history\\nlistCoordinates - Lists all matching GAV coordinates (one per line) honoring -Pcoordinates filter; use -PstrictCoordinates=true for strict matching\\nlistLibraryJars - Lists resolved tested-library JARs for matching coordinates (one per line)\\nmergeNativeTraceMetadata - Merges runtime metadata trace output directories with native-image-utils generate\\npopulateArtifactURLs - Uses a coding agent command to fill source-code-url, repository-url, test-code-url, documentation-url, description, and language in matching metadata index entries.\\npullAllowedDockerImages - Computes and pulls allowed docker images required by matching coordinates\\nscaffold - Creates a metadata and test scaffold for the given coordindates\\nsplitTestOnlyMetadata - Moves test-only entries from library reachability metadata into test resources metadata.\\n\\nPublishing tasks\\n----------------\\npackage - Packages current repository to 'build/graalvm-reachability-metadata-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT.zip'\\n\\nVerification tasks\\n------------------\\ncheck - Runs all checks.\\ncheckDocLinks - Verifies that every repo-local link in Markdown documentation resolves\\ncheckstyle - Runs checkstyle on all subprojects\\ndiff - Tests GraalVM Reflection Metadata that was changed between 'baseCommit' and 'newCommit'\\njacocoTestReport - Generates JaCoCo coverage reports for all subprojects (runs tests first)\\njavaTest - Runs JVM tests (Gradle 'test') for all subprojects\\nrunNativeTraceImage - Runs trace-enabled native tests once for matching coordinates\\nspotlessApply - Applies code formatting steps to sourcecode in-place.\\nspotlessCheck - Checks that sourcecode satisfies formatting steps.\\nspotlessDiagnose\\ntckTest - Runs Native Image tests for all matching coordinates (TCK)\\ntest - Aggregates tests configured by the TCK harness\\ntestAllInfra - Determines one artifact coordinate via generateInfrastructureChangedCoordinatesMatrix (or uses -Pcoordinate/-Pcoordinates if provided), then runs testInfra for that coordinate and also for 1/64. Options: -Pparallelism to control concurrency.\\ntestInfra - Runs clean and pullAllowedDockerImages, then runs (validateIndexFiles, checkstyle, spotlessCheck, checkMetadataFiles, fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions, test, jacocoTestReport, listLibraryJars, generateDynamicAccessReport, generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport, generateLibraryStats, listCoordinates, generateDependencyGraph, splitTestOnlyMetadata) concurrently with isolated logs for a single coordinate.\\n                        Options: -Pcoordinate or -Pcoordinates to specify the target; -Pparallelism to control the number of concurrent tasks.\\nvalidateIndexFiles - Checks content of index.json files for matching coordinates or files\\nvalidateLibraryStats - Validates exploded stats/*.json files against the committed JSON schema\\n\\nOther tasks\\n-----------\\nprepareKotlinBuildScriptModel\\nspotlessGroovy\\nspotlessGroovyApply\\nspotlessGroovyCheck\\nspotlessGroovyDiagnose\\nspotlessGroovyGradle\\nspotlessGroovyGradleApply\\nspotlessGroovyGradleCheck\\nspotlessGroovyGradleDiagnose\\nspotlessInternalRegisterDependencies\\nspotlessJava\\nspotlessJavaApply\\nspotlessJavaCheck\\nspotlessJavaDiagnose\\nspotlessJson\\nspotlessJsonApply\\nspotlessJsonCheck\\nspotlessJsonDiagnose\\nspotlessPython\\nspotlessPythonApply\\nspotlessPythonCheck\\nspotlessPythonDiagnose\\nspotlessShell\\nspotlessShellApply\\nspotlessShellCheck\\nspotlessShellDiagnose\\n\\nRules\\n-----\\nPattern: clean<TaskName>: Cleans the output files of a task.\\nPattern: build<ConfigurationName>: Assembles the artifacts of a configuration.\\n\\n[Incubating] Problems report is available at: file:///home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_workt